{"content":"---\ntitle: \"How to: Bind an Adorner to an Element | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.prod: \".net-framework\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"dotnet-wpf\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"UIElements, binding adorners to\"\n  - \"adorners, binding to specified UIElements\"\nms.assetid: b2101611-a0ee-4137-bdb8-9b3673d2e6b9\ncaps.latest.revision: 10\nauthor: dotnet-bot\nms.author: dotnetcontent\nmanager: \"wpickett\"\n---\n# How to: Bind an Adorner to an Element\nThis example shows how to programmatically bind an adorner to a specified <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>.  \n  \n## Example  \n To bind an adorner to a particular <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>, follow these steps:  \n  \n1.  Call the `static` method <xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer.GetAdornerLayer%2A> to get an <xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer> object for the <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> to be adorned. <xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer.GetAdornerLayer%2A> walks up the visual tree, starting at the specified **UIElement**, and returns the first adorner layer it finds. (If no adorner layers are found, the method returns null.)  \n  \n2.  Call the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer.Add%2A> method to bind the adorner to the target **UIElement**.  \n  \n The following example binds a SimpleCircleAdorner (shown above) to a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox> named *myTextBox*.  \n  \n [!code-csharp[Adorners_SimpleCircleAdorner#_AdornSingleElement](../../../../samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_Wpf/Adorners_SimpleCircleAdorner/CSharp/Window1.xaml.cs#_adornsingleelement)]\n [!code-vb[Adorners_SimpleCircleAdorner#_AdornSingleElement](../../../../samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_Wpf/Adorners_SimpleCircleAdorner/VisualBasic/Window1.xaml.vb#_adornsingleelement)]  \n  \n> [!NOTE]\n>  Using [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xaml](../../../../includes/tlasharptla-xaml-md.md)] to bind an adorner to another element is currently not supported.  \n  \n## See Also  \n [Adorners Overview](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/controls/adorners-overview.md)","nodes":[{"pos":[12,66],"content":"How to: Bind an Adorner to an Element | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"How to: Bind an Adorner to an Element | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,54]}]},{"pos":[482,519],"content":"How to: Bind an Adorner to an Element","linkify":"How to: Bind an Adorner to an Element","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Bind an Adorner to an Element","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"This example shows how to programmatically bind an adorner to a specified <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.UIElement&gt;</ph>.","pos":[520,626],"source":"This example shows how to programmatically bind an adorner to a specified <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>."},{"pos":[635,642],"content":"Example","linkify":"Example","nodes":[{"content":"Example","pos":[0,7]}]},{"content":"To bind an adorner to a particular <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.UIElement&gt;</ph>, follow these steps:","pos":[646,733],"source":"To bind an adorner to a particular <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>, follow these steps:"},{"content":"Call the <ph id=\"ph1\">`static`</ph> method <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer.GetAdornerLayer%2A&gt;</ph> to get an <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer&gt;</ph> object for the <ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.UIElement&gt;</ph> to be adorned.","pos":[743,948],"source":"Call the `static` method <xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer.GetAdornerLayer%2A> to get an <xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer> object for the <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> to be adorned."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Documents.AdornerLayer.GetAdornerLayer%2A&gt;</ph> walks up the visual tree, starting at the specified <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>UIElement<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and returns the first ad